    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I7b22badb37568a5d3a1c93999fca0e6ee35199d1
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I7b22badb37568a5d3a1c93999fca0e6ee35199d1
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: I7b22badb37568a5d3a1c93999fca0e6ee35199d1
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I8d51f499bf31e4f9d0d5f539621207cb35356072
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: I93c1f2dcad3585596cb59afde935312ea15dc81e
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I2b2ebefc60e05b307184fbadf01b41f9e6ecd37b
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty
    
    Change-Id: Id742d02d92ab6421949fe3ca02f234bec463299f

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Jersey 2.X.

    Change-Id: Ib55e4920110fba5a50d08949b8a993f5cd7e825a
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty

    Signed-off-by: Gao Kai <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty
    
    Change-Id: Id742d02d92ab6421949fe3ca02f234bec463299f

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I5e939a1d403f7710cbec75ac9d65d7038fa1e2e4
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.
    
    Change-Id: Ia1ee3b9c9c07a1678820c81e46e437ae18b6d72f

    depends on l2switch-hosttracker and alto-manual-maps service.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522
    
    Change-Id: I494aacad440bfd7b103dcc32861890b163e1b3b4

    Change-Id: I8025f68b94d6192c7f7dcbce63a40f16b005e16f
    Signed-off-by: Thanh Ha <thanh.ha@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty

    Change-Id: I167b591432b13ba21d2bf53bd5c514605cbed965
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I5e939a1d403f7710cbec75ac9d65d7038fa1e2e4
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: I8fcaf194ca3c1b8ab3b4dfda35d8fffc12e9109b
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I8fcaf194ca3c1b8ab3b4dfda35d8fffc12e9109b
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I9e333b1dc54f90dbf8ef838152cdfc2d785639d6
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Bump versions by x.(y+1).z for next dev cycle
    
    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Signed-off-by: Y.Jace Liu <yang.jace.liu@linux.com>
    Remove some duplicate code in simple-pce
    
        There are 2 route checkers: MaxBandwidthPathRouteChecker and
        ShortestRouteChecker. The procedure of constraints check share
        the same code. This patch extract the shared code into a single
        function, and move the function to a parent class.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I8fcaf194ca3c1b8ab3b4dfda35d8fffc12e9109b
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I9e333b1dc54f90dbf8ef838152cdfc2d785639d6
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Bump versions by x.(y+1).z for next dev cycle
    
    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I8fcaf194ca3c1b8ab3b4dfda35d8fffc12e9109b
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I93c1f2dcad3585596cb59afde935312ea15dc81e
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I15c82d34a1cfeef14ceb43aacc9d59758d71ad15
    Signed-off-by: Shawn Lin <x.shawn.lin@gmail.com>
    Signed-off-by: Kai Gao <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ia4edacd9318a5d04dc6f32e43f5e2618fd7991f0
    Signed-off-by: Y.Jace Liu <yang.jace.liu@linux.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: I9e333b1dc54f90dbf8ef838152cdfc2d785639d6
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: I9e333b1dc54f90dbf8ef838152cdfc2d785639d6
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    Change-Id: Ieb92a4f64e9ec0eeaecb93665b2819473f2532b9
    Signed-off-by: Anil Belur <abelur@linuxfoundation.org>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.

    Change-Id: I15c82d34a1cfeef14ceb43aacc9d59758d71ad15
    Signed-off-by: Shawn Lin <x.shawn.lin@gmail.com>
    Signed-off-by: Kai Gao <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: I93c1f2dcad3585596cb59afde935312ea15dc81e
    Signed-off-by: Tom Pantelis <tompantelis@gmail.com>
    Use unified namespaces for core/basic/ext modules
    
    urn:opendaylight:alto:core -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.

    urn:opendaylight:alto:basic -> urn:alto
    urn:opendaylight:alto:ext -> urn:alto
    
    This approach is to avoid future conflicts when some experimental
    features become part of the standard protocol.
    
    This patch also comes with a bash script to help with the migration.
    
    Change-Id: Ia1ee3b9c9c07a1678820c81e46e437ae18b6d72f
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Support default auto-maps service
    
    Support one-group auto networkmap as default auto-maps. Initiate
    default ird for ird root and manual-maps. Current implementation
    depends on l2switch-hosttracker and alto-manual-maps service.

    Change-Id: I8fcaf194ca3c1b8ab3b4dfda35d8fffc12e9109b
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ic4cfc9293faad6471cf0883aead3b684faa375b7
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty

    Change-Id: I8fcaf194ca3c1b8ab3b4dfda35d8fffc12e9109b
    Signed-off-by: Kai GAO <gaok12@mails.tsinghua.edu.cn>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522

    Change-Id: Ic4cfc9293faad6471cf0883aead3b684faa375b7
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Add the northbound exception handler
    
    Handle ALTO Protocol Errors defined in RFC7285 8.5. Add a class to
    generate error information response and implement the checker of
    endpoint property service's requests.
    
     - Exceptions are defined in alto/core/northbound/api/exception
    
     - Exception handler is in alto/core/northbound/impl/
    
     - The example of how to use the handler can be found  in
       alto-core/standard-northbound-routes/endpointproperty

    Change-Id: Id4eec06e09ba6ace6a282d57259cefdc4352ee02
    Signed-off-by: jensenzhang <jingxuan.n.zhang@gmail.com>
    Add missing <name> fields for pom.xml files
    
    This is used by autorelease scripts to automatically parse which project
    is failing a build and report to the mailing list automatically. We need
    names in the format:
    
        ODL :: <groupId> :: <artifactId>
    
    This patch formats in the same format as found in the startup archetypes
    patch found here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/52522
